name: Decidueye
description: As if wielding a bow, it launches the arrow quills hidden among the feathers of its wings. Decidueye's shots never miss.

name: Dedenne
description: Its upper whiskers are sensors that survey its surroundings. Its lower whiskers are organs that shoot electricity.

name: Girafarig
description: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent by biting.

name: Nidorina
description: It has a calm and caring nature. Because its horn grows slowly, it prefers not to fight.

name: Sinistea
description: This Pokémon is said to have been born when a lonely spirit possessed a cold, leftover cup of tea.

name: Cyndaquil
description: It has a timid nature. If it is startled, the flames on its back burn more vigorously.

name: Chewtle
description: It starts off battles by attacking with its rock-hard horn, but as soon as the opponent flinches, this Pokémon bites down and never lets go.

name: Cinderace
description: It's skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.

name: Spiritomb
description: It was bound to a fissure in an Odd Keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.

name: Chewtle
description: Apparently the itch of its teething impels it to snap its jaws at anything in front of it.

name: Spheal
description: Its body is covered in fluffy fur. The fur keeps it from feeling cold while it is rolling on ice.

name: Scraggy
description: It protects itself with its durable skin. It's thought that this Pokémon will evolve once its skin has completely stretched out.

name: Lycanroc
description: They live alone without forming packs. They will only listen to orders from Trainers who can draw out their true power.

name: Sandaconda
description: When it contracts its body, over 220 pounds of sand sprays from its nose. If it ever runs out of sand, it becomes disheartened.

name: Galarian Obstagoon
description: It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.

name: Sandslash
description: Thanks to its thick claws, it's good at climbing trees. There are plenty of Sandslash that park themselves in trees and go right to sleep.

name: Clobbopus
description: Its tentacles tear off easily, but it isn't alarmed when that happens—it knows they'll grow back. It's about as smart as a three-year-old.

name: Gyarados
description: They say that during past strife, Gyarados would appear and leave blazing ruins in its wake.

name: Hitmonlee
description: The legs freely contract and stretch. The stretchy legs allow it to hit a distant foe with a rising kick.

name: Scizor
description: Its wings are not used for flying. They are flapped at high speed to adjust its body temperature.

name: Passimian
description: Passimian live in groups of about 20, with each member performing an assigned role. Through cooperation, the group survives.

name: Drakloak
description: It's capable of flying faster than 120 mph. It battles alongside Dreepy and dotes on them until they successfully evolve.

name: Grapploct
description: Searching for an opponent to test its skills against, it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over, it returns to the sea.

name: Sinistea
description: This Pokémon is said to have been born when a lonely spirit possessed a cold, leftover cup of tea.

name: Cherrim
description: The faint scent that emanates from its full blossom entices bug Pokémon to it.

name: Toxel
description: It manipulates the chemical makeup of its poison to produce electricity. The voltage is weak, but it can cause a tingling paralysis.

name: Rolycoly
description: Most of its body has the same composition as coal. Fittingly, this Pokémon was first discovered in coal mines about 400 years ago.
